France and Germany, Europe’s two most powerful countries, have been hit hard by the coronavirus, with each approaching 150,000 confirmed cases.
If there’s a lesson for world governments, then, it’s to be more like Germany — not France.
How Germany kept its coronavirus death rate so lowIt’s not surprising that Germany has the world’s fifth-largest coronavirus outbreak.
It also helped that the vast majority of early cases were clustered in the western region of Heinsberg.
How France bungled its coronavirus responseFrance, like Germany, is a wealthy country with a great health care system.